From e37a49ab9a81da0010c11e37067cb42647d3a9d3 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Jeevan Kukkalli <jeevank@qti.qualcomm.com>
Date: Sat, 19 Jul 2025 11:46:06 +0530
Subject: [PATCH 7/9] UPSTREAM: DP: wifi: ath12k: Enable low threshold
 interrupt for rx mon buffer ring

Currently, monitor buffer ring replenishment is triggered during the
reaping of monitor status and packet buffers. In the case of packet
buffers, this replenishment occurs per buffer, requiring the ring lock to
be taken for each individual buffer. This results in significant lock
contention and performance overhead, especially under high traffic
conditions.

To address this inefficiency, move the monitor descriptor to the free list
immediately after processing. Driver fetches descriptor from the free list
and populate the used list only when a low water mark interrupt is
received from the hardware. This interrupt is configured to trigger when
the number of available entries falls below half the total, ensuring timely
replenishment without excessive locking.

Additionally, the monitor source ring is currently configured with 4K
entries, while the monitor destination ring has 8K entries. This imbalance
leads to fewer available source buffers compared to destination buffers,
increasing the risk of backpressure due to source buffer exhaustion.

This change lays the groundwork for upcoming enhancements where monitor
destination ring processing will be handled in a workqueue context. This
future work will enable TLV parsing and packet delivery to mac80211 to
occur in process context, further improving performance during monitor
mode.

Patch-dependency:
0475-06-Upstream-DP-wifi-ath12k-add-drop-tlv-handling-while-.patch

Signed-off-by: Jeevan Kukkalli <jeevank@qti.qualcomm.com>
Signed-off-by: P Praneesh <ppranees@qti.qualcomm.com>
